review_blob: Pours very nicely. Did not get too much head. The taste was strong but not overpowering. Got to love the higher alcohol content. I did not serve in a snifter, but enjoyed it out of a pint glass.
The beer pours into a nice head. First taste was a nice IPA with a ton of hops. The taste moves on to the floral hops is a bit  overwhelming by the end of the glass.
Floral aroma with the right amount of hops this beer is great for the summer.

The celebrator I liked as a double bock a bit more than the others. I do taste the breadish flavor. All in all pretty good beer for sipping on and with a meal. Holding it up to the light its a red/brown tint with a strong flavor.
